================================================================================
Third-party components and data
================================================================================

Riprap incorporates and depends on third-party open-source software,
foundation models, and public-record datasets. Each retains its own
upstream licence; the list below records attribution where required.

Foundation models (Apache 2.0 unless noted):
  - IBM Granite 4.1 (granite-4.1-h-tiny, granite-4.1-h-small)
  - IBM Granite Embedding 278M (granite-embedding-278m-multilingual)
  - IBM Granite TimeSeries TTM r2 (granite-timeseries-ttm-r2)
  - IBM Mellea (rejection-sampling validator)
  - NASA / IBM Prithvi-EO 2.0
  - IBM / ESA TerraMind 1.0

NYC-specialised fine-tunes published by this project (Apache 2.0):
  - msradam/TerraMind-NYC-Adapters (LULC, Buildings, TiM LoRA family)
  - msradam/Prithvi-EO-2.0-NYC-Pluvial
  - msradam/Granite-TTM-r2-Battery-Surge

Public-record data sources contacted at runtime (no commercial APIs):
  See the "Data sources" table in README.md and the licence map in
  ARCHITECTURE.md for hosting agency, access terms, and vintage.

Logo attribution:
  The Riprap dam mark is derived from "Dam" by Chintuza, via the
  Noun Project (https://thenounproject.com/icon/dam-4516918/),
  licensed CC-BY 3.0. The original SVG embedded the attribution as
  on-canvas text; assets/logo*.svg in this repository strip the
  embedded text and carry the attribution here per the Creative
  Commons attribution requirement.

================================================================================
AI-assisted authoring
================================================================================

Portions of the source code, configuration, prompt templates, and
documentation in this repository were drafted with the assistance of large
language models. All output was reviewed and accepted by Adam Rahman, who
takes responsibility for the resulting code, claims, and reproducibility
guarantees made by this project.

The Riprap system orchestrates third-party foundation models (IBM Granite
4.1, IBM Granite Embedding 278M, NASA-IBM Prithvi-EO 2.0, IBM Granite TTM r2,
IBM-ESA TerraMind 1.0) at inference time. It does not generate model
weights. The NYC fine-tunes referenced by this system are trained
separately and documented at github.com/msradam/riprap-models.

This repository's initial commit consolidates work developed across many
commits in the project's working repository (msradam/riprap-nyc) between
May and July 2026, starting with the AMD Developer Cloud hackathon
(May 4-10, 2026) and continuing through the open-source release cut here.
That working history — including any "Co-Authored-By" trailers referencing
Anthropic Claude on individual commits — lives in msradam/riprap-nyc, not
in this repository's git log. This NOTICE is the artifact-level disclosure
for what ships here.
